{"type":"message","id":"30884396","parentId":"e43b7b30","timestamp":"2026-06-19T20:51:31.373Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Task: Fix [medium] UI/UX: JS-only SPA provides no <noscript> fallback for users without JavaScript\n## Step: execute\n\n### wwwroot/index.html\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n    <title>File Browser</title>\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"dist/app.css\" />\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div id=\"app\"></div>\n    <script type=\"module\" src=\"dist/app.js\"></script>\n</body>\n</html>\n\n```\nYou are a fix agent. Resolve the following final-review finding.\n\nReview dimension: UI/UX\nSeverity: medium\nFile: wwwroot/index.html:9-11\nTitle: JS-only SPA provides no <noscript> fallback for users without JavaScript\n\nFinding:\nThe new index.html renders an empty `<div id=\"app\"></div>` and depends entirely on `<script type=\"module\" src=\"dist/app.js\">` to populate the UI. If JavaScript is disabled, blocked, or fails to load/parse (e.g., a build artifact is missing, a CSP blocks modules, or the user is on an assistive-tech environment with scripts turned off), the page is completely blank with no explanation. This is a real accessibility/usability defect: affected users cannot tell why the screen is empty or that the app requires JavaScript. The fix is to add a `<noscript>` element inside `<body>` with a brief, actionable message telling the user the app requires JavaScript to function.\n\nFix instructions (follow exactly; make targeted, minimal changes):\nIn the file `wwwroot/index.html`, add a `<noscript>` fallback inside the `<body>` element so that users with JavaScript disabled see an explanatory message instead of a blank page. Immediately after the `<div id=\"app\"></div>` line (and before or after the `<script>` tag), insert:\n\n    <noscript>\n        <p style=\"color: #e6e6e6; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif; padding: 16px;\">File Browser requires JavaScript to run. Please enable JavaScript in your browser settings and reload the page.</p>\n    </noscript>\n\nKeep the existing markup, viewport meta, charset, title, stylesheet link, and module script unchanged. The message should be plain text (no interactive controls) and styled to be visible against the dark background defined in `dist/app.css`."}],"timestamp":1781902291373}}
